## 5. Quick Start / Usage Examples\par
\par
Below are simplified examples of how to generate batches of random numbers using the three different backend approaches provided by Ultimate RNG.\par
\par
### 5.1. Job System / Burst Compiler (High Performance C#)\par
\par
This approach is highly recommended for most Unity standard use cases where you need heavy random generation without leaving C#.\par
\par
```csharp\par
using Cet.Rng.Job;\par
using Unity.Collections;\par
using UnityEngine;\par
\par
public class JobRngExample : MonoBehaviour\par
\{\par
    void Start()\par
    \{\par
        int count = 1_000_000;\par
        uint seed = 12345;\par
\par
        // Create a sequence generator with Persistent allocator\par
        using var rng = new Xoshiro256SsSeq(count, Allocator.Persistent);\par
\par
        // Fill the internal buffer with random numbers.\par
        // This is extremely fast and can also be run parallel (FillParallel).\par
        rng.Fill(count, seed);\par
\par
        // The numbers are now ready to be used from the NativeArray inside the sequence.\par
        // For instance, passing rng.Result to other IJobParallelFor jobs.\par
    \}\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
### 5.2. Rust Native Plugin (Cryptographic-like Quality)\par
\par
When you need the absolute highest statistical quality or specific algorithms like SFMT.\par
\par
```csharp\par
using Cet.Rng;\par
using UnityEngine;\par
\par
public class RustNativeExample : MonoBehaviour\par
\{\par
    void Start()\par
    \{\par
        int count = 1_000_000;\par
        uint seed = 42;\par
\par
        // Initialize Native PRNG (e.g. SIMD-oriented Fast MT)\par
        using var sfmt = new Sfmt1993764(seed);\par
\par
        // Generate a large batch into a NativeArray/Span efficiently\par
        var randomFloats = sfmt.NextF64s(count);\par
\par
        Debug.Log($"Generated \{randomFloats.Length\} random numbers!");\par
    \}\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
### 5.3. Compute Shader (GPU Generation)\par
\par
Ideal for offloading extreme workloads to the GPU.\par
\par
```csharp\par
using Cet.Rng.Gpu;\par
using UnityEngine;\par
\par
public class GpuRngExample : MonoBehaviour\par
\{\par
    // Assign via Inspector\par
    public Philox32Gpu philox32;\par
\par
    void Start()\par
    \{\par
        int count = 1_000_000;\par
        uint seed = 999;\par
        var results = new float[count];\par
\par
        // Initialize with seed\par
        philox32.Init(seed);\par
\par
        // Dispatch Compute Shader to generate random floats natively on GPU\par
        philox32.GetRandomFloats(results, 0, 1);\par
\par
        Debug.Log($"First GPU Random: \{results[0]\}");\par
    \}\par
\}\par
```\par
